name: Strawberries
description: Juicy and sweet strawberries perfect for adding a burst of flavor to your desserts, salads, and smoothies.

careInformation.wateringRequirements: Keep soil consistently moist, but not waterlogged.
careInformation.sunlightRequirements: Full sun (at least 6 hours of direct sunlight per day).
careInformation.fertilization: Fertilize with a balanced fertilizer every 4-6 weeks during the growing season.
careInformation.pruning: Remove any dead leaves and runners to encourage healthy growth.
careInformation.pestsAndDiseases: Susceptible to slugs, aphids, and mold. Regularly inspect and treat as needed.

additionalInformation.seasonality: Best planted in early spring; fruits ripen in late spring to early summer.
additionalInformation.hardiness: Hardy to temperatures down to 20°F; mulch in winter for protection in colder climates.
additionalInformation.uses: Ideal for fresh eating, making jams, and adding to desserts and salads.

name: Apple Plant
description: A delightful apple plant that produces crisp and sweet apples, perfect for snacking, baking, and making cider.

careInformation.wateringRequirements: Water deeply once a week, more often in hot weather.
careInformation.sunlightRequirements: Full sun (at least 6 hours of direct sunlight per day).
careInformation.fertilization: Fertilize in early spring and mid-summer with a balanced fertilizer.
careInformation.pruning: Prune in late winter to remove dead or weak branches and to shape the plant.
careInformation.pestsAndDiseases: Susceptible to apple scab, fire blight, and codling moth. Regularly inspect and treat as needed.

additionalInformation.seasonality: Flowers in spring; fruits ripen in late summer to early fall.
additionalInformation.hardiness: Hardy to temperatures down to -30°F; mulch in winter for extra protection in colder climates.
additionalInformation.toxicity: Non-toxic to humans and pets, but apple seeds contain small amounts of cyanide and should not be consumed in large quantities.
additionalInformation.uses: Ideal for fresh eating, baking, making cider, and adding to salads.
